JDBC = Java Database Connectivity
Java se database (MySQL/Postgres) se baat karne ka tareeka

PreparedStatement kya hota hai?
👉 SQL query ko safe aur dynamic banane ka tareeka

Tera current code (galat / risky)
String sql = "INSERT INTO student (name, email) VALUES ('" + name + "', '" + email + "')";

👉 Problem:
- SQL Injection risk 😵
- Unsafe
- Performance bhi bekaar

✅ Correct way (PreparedStatement)
String sql = "INSERT INTO student (name, email) VALUES (?, ?)";

PreparedStatement pstmt = conn.prepareStatement(sql);

pstmt.setString(1, name);
pstmt.setString(2, email);

pstmt.executeUpdate();

🧠 Samajh
👉 ? = placeholder
👉 setString() = value fill karna



Transactions kya hota hai?
👉 Multiple operations ko ek group me run karna

🧠 Simple Example
👉 Tu 2 kaam kar raha:
1. User create
2. Balance update

👉 Agar:
Step 1 success
Step 2 fail
👉 Toh pura system gadbad ❌

🔥 Solution = Transaction
👉 Either:
dono kaam ho ✅
ya dono cancel ❌

Example:
conn.setAutoCommit(false);

try {
    insertStudents(conn, "A", "a@gmail.com");
    updateStudents(conn, 1, "B", "b@gmail.com");

    conn.commit(); // sab successful
} catch (Exception e) {
    conn.rollback(); // sab cancel
}

commit() → save permanently
rollback() → sab undo

